node.text:
I’ve been slacking the past few weeks with coming back to city/supporting local restaurants 🍝 🍝 🍝 and moving to a new apartment but I’m ready to jump back into my normal diet routine. We’ll start w answers to frequently asked Qs

• Do is snack? 
Nope, or as little as possible.

• How many days a week do I drink?
-The honest answer is yes, about 2 to 3 times a week. I prefer tequila with lime over everything else and max out at 4 cocktails on a wild night 🧃
-I do drink wine, but try to make it red, and sparingly because of the sugar (plus I feel sick really easily w wine)

Breakfast 
• make it a @bewellbykelly smoothie! I’ve adopted Kelly’s method in the past 14 months and I feel so comfortable in my body. 
• I like bovine + eggshell protein powder bc it’s a complete amino acid (20-26g per serving)
• any Kelly smoothie is a balance of fat, fiber, protein that keeps you full for hours

Lunch
• rinse and repeat raw veggie salad •
I’m obsessed with this salad because it’s not sooo restrictive (hello I fuck with ranch dressing and fried chicken)
• mix together 2 cups of raw organic veggies (broccoli, radish, carrot, cucumber, etc etc)
• half an avo
• add nuts (I like sunflower seeds)
• add some homemade ranch dressing (almond milk, avocado mayo + seasoning)
**toss it all together! Remember, this diet is LOW gluten and dairy, not NO gluten and dairy but you can easily substitute out everything you want here. 🤩 I find a low g/d diet when mixed with tons of veggie fiber is also anti-inflammatory but less restrictive so easier to maintain 🤩

Dinner 
• typically I eat at a restaurant or get take-out (hey it’s NYC it’s what we do)
• I always go for some huge salad and I love to mix with an antipasto plate full of olives, meats, cheeses
• if no antipasto I go for a lean protein and if I feel fun add in a side portion of gluten-free pasta 
• this insane dinner in the vid is from my #1 girl @altroparadiso

So there’s ^ what I eat in a day when I’m following my wellness routine. High in veggies and good fats but not so restrictive it can’t be maintained. When I eat this way for a week straight I love how I feel in my body ❤️❣️

node.title: 🥒 what I eat in a day 🫐 - Summer Series!

node.text: I’m curious what your 3 biggest health and wellness concerns are! I’ll go first: dealing with chronic fatigue 😴 • identifying toxicity in the body from chemicals/pollutants/etc 🚛💨• staying on top of weight maintenance 💪🏼. If you’re willing to share drop yours in the comments. I’m all ears and anything you share (via comments here, DMs when I share wellness updates in IG stories, LW product reviews) always helps me shape what we make at @lovewellness and how we think about wellness as the category continues to evolve. ❤️
